德国“截”了瑞士24万只口罩。
Germany "intercepted" 240,000 Swiss face masks.
澎湃新闻                      。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
有内涵的时政新媒体。
Connotation of the new political media.
澎湃新闻记者 南博一随着新冠病毒开始在欧洲蔓延，口罩等防护物资成为了稀缺之物。
Pang reporter Nan Bo Yi as the new crown virus began to spread in Europe, such as respirators become a scarce thing.
一些国家开始禁止对外出口防护物资，一些国家的原材料渠道被因此切断，各国之间矛盾频发。
Some countries began to ban the export of protective materials, some countries have cut off raw materials channels, and contradictions between countries are frequent.
据《新苏黎世报周日版》( NZZ am Sonntag )7日报道，一辆属于瑞士公司的卡车在前往瑞士途中被德国海关拦截，车上有24万个防护口罩。
A truck belonging to a Swiss company with 240,000 face masks was stopped by German customs on its way to Switzerland, the newspaper NZZ am Sonntag reported Sunday.
瑞士联邦经济事务秘书处（SECO）指出，这不是一个单独的案例，秘书处发言人Fabian Maienfisch称：“我们得到的信息是，运输还会进一步受到阻碍。
The Swiss Federal Secretariat for Economic Affairs (SECO) stated that this was not a separate case and that "the information we have received is that transport will be further impeded."
”瑞士联邦经济事务秘书处（SECO）是瑞士政府内处理所有有关经济政策核心问题的管理中心。
The Swiss Federal Secretariat for Economic Affairs (SECO) is the centre of management within the Swiss Government for all issues central to economic policy.
它的宗旨是为企业的发展创造基本的法规与经济政策条件。
Its purpose is to create the basic legal and economic policy conditions for the development of enterprises.
它还为确保瑞士作为商业发展基地的竞争条件提供支持，并帮助瑞士的产品和服务进入所有市场。
It also provides support to ensure competitive conditions for Switzerland as a base for business development and facilitates access to all markets for Swiss products and services.
该机构表示，上述事件发生后，瑞士立即向德国的有关部门进行了抗议。
The agency said that immediately after the incident, Switzerland to the German authorities to protest.
此外，秘书处6日还邀请瑞士驻德国大使就这个问题进行了讨论，敦促德国当局立即对被冻结的货物放行。
In addition, on 6 June, the Secretariat invited the Ambassador of Switzerland to Germany to discuss the issue and urged the German authorities to release the frozen cargo immediately.
世界卫生组织总干事谭德塞3月3日在例行新闻发布会上发出警告：由于全球范围内需求增加以及囤积和不当使用等原因，医用手套、口罩、呼吸器、护目镜、面罩和防护服等价格飙升，供给出现短缺，使得各国的应对能力受到影响。
Medical gloves, masks, respirators, goggles, face masks and protective clothing have surged and supply shortages have affected the ability of countries to respond because of increased demand and hoarding and misuse around the world, the director-general of the World Health Organization (WHO) warned at a regular press conference on Wednesday.
为了保证本国口罩供应，目前，多国已采取措施对口罩进行管制。
Many countries have taken steps to control the supply of face masks in the country.
据报道，德国内政部3月4日宣布，为确保国内在疫情暴发时能有足够供应，即日起禁止对外出口医用口罩及其它医用防护装备。
The German Interior Ministry announced on March 4 that it would ban the export of medical masks and other medical protective equipment to ensure adequate supplies in the event of an outbreak.
《新苏黎世报周日版 》指出，这些措施严重影响了几乎不生产任何医疗耗材的瑞士。
According to the Sunday edition of the New Zurich newspaper, these measures have severely affected Switzerland, which produces virtually no medical supplies.
该国市面上的口罩大多来自于远东地区，尤其是中国：德国公司在中国大量订购口罩，瑞士公司从中购买一部分，然后把材料从德国运到瑞士。
Most of the country's masks come from the Far East, especially China: German companies order large quantities of masks in China, and Swiss companies buy some of them and ship them from Germany to Switzerland.
但是现在，这个销售渠道中断了。
But now the distribution channel has broken down.
德国的禁令既影响了对欧盟国家的口罩出口，也影响了对非欧盟国家的出口。
The German ban affects both exports of masks to EU countries and exports to non-EU countries.
目前瑞士的防护口罩供应已经到了紧缺的地步。
The supply of respirators in Switzerland is already in short supply.
瑞士国家感染预防中心（National Center for Infection Prevention）6日通知该国的医院，医生应将口罩的使用期限从两小时延长到八小时。
The National Center for Infection Prevention in Switzerland informed hospitals Tuesday that doctors should extend the use of face masks from two to eight hours.
该中心总裁安德烈亚斯·威德默说：“将湿口罩戴在脸上一天会很不舒服。
"Wet masks can be uncomfortable on your face for a day," said Andreas Willemer, president of the centre.
” 但是，鉴于口罩的供应在减少，这是短期内唯一能够继续保证所需保护的解决方案。
But with the supply of masks dwindling, this is the only solution that will ensure the needed protection in the short term.
此外，瑞士有一个中央防护口罩仓库，将在未来几周陆续将口罩移交给各州。
In addition, Switzerland has a central warehouse for respirators, which will be handed over to the cantons in the coming weeks.
然而，瑞士没有储存防护服的地方。
However, there is no storage area for protective clothing in Switzerland.
当局希望德国能尽快在这场有关医疗防护材料的纠纷中让步。
Authorities hope Germany will soon be able to compromise on the dispute over medical protection material.
除了德国之外，3月3日，法国政府也下令征用该国所有新生产的防护口罩及库存，并将这些口罩分发给医护人员和感染新冠病毒的法国公民。
In addition to Germany, on 3 March, the Government of France also ordered the expropriation of all newly produced face masks and stocks in the country and their distribution to medical personnel and French citizens infected with the new crown virus.
作为欧洲受疫情影响最严重的国家，意大利政府已表态，未经事先许可不允许出口防护设备。
As the worst affected country in Europe, the Italian government has said it will not allow the export of protective equipment without prior permission.
捷克卫生部长亚当·沃伊特希奇（AdamVojtěch）称，该国已要求当地口罩生产商不要出口口罩。
Adam Vojtěch, Czech health minister, says the country has asked local mask makers not to export masks.
这些举动引起了众怒。
These actions provoked public anger.
周五（6日）在布鲁塞尔举行的卫生部长会议上，欧盟各国之间的紧张氛围显而易见。
Tensions between EU countries were apparent at a meeting of health ministers in Brussels on Friday.
据美国政治新闻网站Politico 3月6日报道，比利时卫生部长Maggie De Block在会上表示，上述国家对于口罩的限制措施阻碍了供应商按合同运送到其他国家。
At the meeting, Belgian Health Minister Maggie De Block said restrictions on masks in those countries were preventing suppliers from shipping to other countries as contracted.
她说：“我们不会对这场疫情反应过度，因此我会坚持：比利时不会对防护物资实施出口禁令。
"We will not overreact to the epidemic, so I will insist that Belgium does not impose an export ban on protective goods," she said.
荷兰，立陶宛，爱沙尼亚和奥地利等国家也对此表示赞同。
Countries such as the Netherlands, Lithuania, Estonia and Austria also supported this approach.
